fields.Title: CONTAINERYARD / PANEL
fields.Description: very likely we need this panel to make mega-rich-light-bendy-guy container move.

fields.Title: You: "[Leave.]"
fields.Dialogue Text: [Leave.]

fields.Title: Encyclopedia: "*Marche* -- On. *Arrêt* -- Off."
fields.Dialogue Text: *Marche* -- On. *Arrêt* -- Off.

fields.Title: Crane Control Panel: "No screech of metal when you push t..."
fields.Dialogue Text: No screech of metal when you push the button this time. Only silence, as the crane remains in its state of dormancy.

fields.Title: Crane Control Panel: "The crane does not return to its or..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The crane does not return to its original position. It does not move at all.

fields.Title: Crane Control Panel: "With a loud grind the crane shifts..."
fields.Dialogue Text: With a loud grind the crane shifts overhead, moving a massive metal container through the air...

fields.Title: You: "Understood. Let's get back to the p..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Understood. Let's get back to the panel.

fields.Title: Perception (Smell): "A faint smell of burning rubber rea..."
fields.Dialogue Text: A faint smell of burning rubber reaches your nostrils. A short-circuit.

fields.Title: Inland Empire: "This crane was built with a purpose..."
fields.Dialogue Text: This crane was built with a purpose which has now been fulfilled -- to move *this* container.

fields.Title: You: "Press *Arrêt*."
fields.Dialogue Text: Press *Arrêt*.

fields.Title: You: "Understood. Let's get back to the p..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Understood. Let's get back to the panel.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""I can't see how that was worth the..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I can't see how that was worth the ruckus..." He looks at the crate. "Except for seeing the crane in action. Which, I admit, was satisfying."

fields.Title: You: "Its purpose? What do you mean?"
fields.Dialogue Text: Its purpose? What do you mean?

fields.Title: Interfacing: "The harbour sleeps as the strike ra..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The harbour sleeps as the strike rages in the distance. The crane can rest again, now that its purpose has been fulfilled.

fields.Title: Inland Empire: "If only you knew..."
fields.Dialogue Text: If only you knew...

fields.Title: You: "What's inside the container?"
fields.Dialogue Text: What's inside the container?

fields.Title: You: "Press *Marche*."
fields.Dialogue Text: Press *Marche*.

fields.Title: Inland Empire: "Who can say? All you know is -- it'..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Who can say? All you know is -- it's special.

fields.Title: Crane Control Panel: "A rusting control panel with severa..."
fields.Dialogue Text: A rusting control panel with several knobs. Two buttons, marked *Marche* and *Arrêt*, are faded with use. It seems to control the large crane above -- a container is attached to its hook block.

fields.Title: Crane Control Panel: "... and with a surprisingly quiet t..."
fields.Dialogue Text: ... and with a surprisingly quiet thunk, the crane places the container down.

fields.Title: Interfacing: "The rusty control panel grows warm..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The rusty control panel grows warm to the touch. Then grows cold. It is finished.

fields.Title: Interfacing: "Moving *this* container, of course...."
fields.Dialogue Text: Moving *this* container, of course. For this purpose it was built; for this purpose it has acted. And now it will rest.

fields.Title: Crane Control Panel: "The crane stands tall: proud, erect..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The crane stands tall: proud, erect and *still*.

fields.Title: Crane Control Panel: "A rusting control panel with severa..."
fields.Dialogue Text: A rusting control panel with several knobs. The words *Marche* and *Arrêt* are -- very, very slightly -- even more faded with use.
